 or 2 layers of muslin cloth and set over a large bowl. Pour mixture into simmering basket and allow to drain for at least 30 minutes. Do not squeeze liquid from ricotta. Set drained ricotta (approx. 300-340 g) aside in a bowl. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ricotta gnocchi"},{"content":"Place Parmesan cheese into mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>."},{"content":"Add flour, egg, salt, nutmeg and all of the reserved ricotta (approx. 300-340 g) and knead 30 sec\/, or until just combined, prolong time if necessary."},{"content":"Transfer dough onto a silicone bread mat or lightly floured work surface and gently work into a ball, then divide into 4 portions. Roll each portion into a thin sausage shape, then cut into pieces (approx. 1 cm in length) using spatula. If desired, gently score gnocchi by rolling pieces over the tines of a fork. Transfer into a bowl and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Gnocchi sauce"},{"content":"Preheat oven to 180°C. Line a baking tray with baking paper and set aside."},{"content":"Place Parmesan cheese and lemon zest into mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>. Transfer into a small bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place sunflower seeds, pumpkin seeds and capers into mixing bowl and combine <b>5 sec\/\/speed 3<b>. Transfer onto prepared baking tray and bake for 15 minutes (180°C), or until lightly golden and toasted. Set aside to cool slightly."},{"content":"Place pancetta and oil into mixing bowl and sauté <b>10 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>, placing simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid."},{"content":"Scrape down sides and base of mixing bowl with spatula, and cook <b>5 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>. Transfer pancetta into a bowl. Discard oil, then place pancetta back into mixing bowl."},{"content":"Add tomatoes, lemon juice, silverbeet and pepper, and cook <b>3 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>. Transfer into a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl a